                <outline text="Deploy or Manage">
                    <outline text="Multichain #workshop #CI7100 #CI7160 #todo ">
                        <outline text="**Step 1: Download Multichain**">
                            <outline text="1. Visit the [Multichain website](https://www.multichain.com/download-install/) and navigate to the download section (choose 'Community Download')."/>
                            <outline text="2. Choose the appropriate version for Windows/Linux and click on the download link."/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="**Step 2: Installation**">
                            <outline text="1. Once the download is complete, locate the downloaded file (usually a .zip file) and extract its contents to a preferred location on your Windows machine."/>
                            <outline text="2. Open Command Prompt by searching for &quot;cmd&quot; in the Windows search bar and selecting &quot;Command Prompt.&quot;"/>
                            <outline text="3. Navigate to the directory where Multichain was extracted using the `cd` command in Command Prompt. For instance, if Multichain is in the Downloads folder, type `cd Downloads\Multichain-x.x.x` (replace x.x.x with the specific version number)."/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="**Step 3: Create a New Blockchain**">
                            <outline text="1. Use the Command Prompt to initiate a new blockchain. Use the following command:">
<outline text="```multichain-util create &lt;chain-name&gt;```"/>
<outline text="Replace `&lt;chain-name&gt;` with your preferred name for the blockchain."/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="2. Navigate to the newly created directory for your blockchain:">
<outline text="```cd &lt;chain-name&gt;```"/>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="**Step 4: Start the Blockchain**">
                            <outline text="1. To start the blockchain, use the following command:">
<outline text="```multichaind &lt;chain-name&gt; -daemon```"/>
<outline text="This will launch the blockchain in the background (daemon mode)."/>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="**Step 5: Interacting with the Blockchain**">
                            <outline text="1. To interact with your Multichain blockchain, use the Multichain command-line interface (CLI). Access it using the following command:">
<outline text="```multichain-cli &lt;chain-name&gt;```"/>
<outline text="This command will open the CLI, allowing you to execute commands for managing your blockchain (e.g., creating assets, issuing permissions, etc.)."/>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="**Step 6: Stopping the Blockchain**">
                            <outline text="1. To stop the Multichain blockchain, use the following command in Command Prompt:">
<outline text="```multichain-cli &lt;chain-name&gt; stop```"/>
<outline text="This will gracefully shut down the blockchain."/>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="**Notes:**">
                            <outline text="Always replace `&lt;chain-name&gt;` with your chosen name for the blockchain throughout the tutorial."/>
                            <outline text="Ensure you follow proper security practices and configurations to protect your blockchain network."/>
                        </outline>
